Package com.hp.jipp.encoding

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Attribute<T>
    An IPP attribute, which is a named, ordered list of 0 or more values.
    AttributeCollection
    An ordered collection of attributes as defined in RFC3382.
    AttributeGroup
    A tagged list of attributes. Only one attribute of a given type may appear in the group, although each attribute may contain 0 or more values.
    AttributeSetType<T>
    A named attribute type which may be used to construct interface Attribute objects containing 0 or more values of type T.
    AttributeType<T>
    A named attribute type which may be used to construct interface Attribute objects containing 0 or one values of type T.
    Codec<T>
    Reads/writes values of T.
    Stringable
    An object that has a native string representation.
    TaggedValue
    Any attribute value which does not directly correspond to a common Java type.

    AttributeImpl<T>
    Overridable implementation for any subclass of interface Attribute.
    AttributeTypeImpl<T>
    A base implementation of interface AttributeType.
    Attributes
    Utilities for the interface Attribute class.
    BooleanType
    An interface AttributeType for a Boolean value.
    CollectionType<T extends AttributeCollection>
    An attribute type for collections of T.
    DateTimeType
    An interface AttributeType for a DateTime value represented as a Calendar object.
    DelimiterTag
    An IPP Delimiter tag.
    EmptyAttribute<T>
    An interface Attribute consisting only of an out-of-band tag and no values.
    EmptyAttributeType<T>
    Type for interface Attributes with no values.
    Enum
    A machine-readable integer code paired with a human-readable name.
    EnumType<T extends Enum>
    An interface AttributeType for an class Enum value.
    IntOrIntRange
    An int or range of int
    IntOrIntRangeType
    An interface AttributeType for a Int or IntRange value.
    IntRangeType
    An interface AttributeType for an IntRange value.
    IntType
    An interface AttributeType for an Int value.
    IppInputStream
    An InputStream which can read IPP packet data.
    IppOutputStream
    An OutputStream for writing an class IppPacket.
    IppPacket
    An IPP packet consisting of header information and zero or more attribute groups.
    KeyValues
    A map of keys to values where keys and values are both strings.
    KeyValuesType
    An interface AttributeType for a value containing class KeyValues pairs.
    KeywordOrName
    Describes an object which may contain either a class Name or a keyword (String).
    KeywordOrNameType
    An interface AttributeType for a class Name or keyword value.
    KeywordType
    An interface AttributeType for a keyword value, represented as a String.
    MediaSizes  
    MutableAttributeGroup
    An interface AttributeGroup which may be altered. Insertion order is preserved.
    Name
    Describes a name object, which may or may not have a language string.
    NameType
    An interface AttributeType for a class Name value.
    OctetsType
    An interface AttributeType for an octetString value represented as a ByteArray.
    OtherOctets
    An attribute value formatted as an array of octets.
    OtherString
    An attribute value formatted as a String.
    OutOfBandTag
    An IPP Out-of-Band Tag.
    Resolution
    Describes a printing resolution.
    ResolutionType
    An interface AttributeType for a class Resolution value.
    ResolutionUnit
    A unit of measurement used to describe resolution.
    StringType
    An interface AttributeType for a value best represented as a String.
    StringableKt  
    Tag
    Value and delimiter tags as specified by RFC2910 and RFC3382
    Text
    Describes a text object, which may or may not have a language string.
    TextType
    An interface AttributeType for a class Text value.
    UnknownAttribute
    An otherwise unrecognized attribute, including at least one value, containing values of any legal type that can be expressed in IPP form.
    UntypedCollection
    An interface AttributeCollection (see RFC3382) represented as a list of interface Attribute objects.
    UntypedEnum
    An enum lacking any formal Enum type (meaning its values cannot be decoded).
    UriType
    An interface AttributeType for a URI value.
    ValueTag
